<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>fr</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>fullrf  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="fullrf"> factorisation de rang plein  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[Q,M,rk]=fullrf(A,[tol])  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>A  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : matrice réelle ou complexe
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>tol  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : nombre réel (tolérance pour le calcul du rang)
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Q,M  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : matrices réelles ou complexes
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>rk  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : entier (rang de <VERB>A</VERB>)
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    Cette fonction calcule la factorisation de rang plein de <VERB>A</VERB> : <VERB>fullrf</VERB> renvoie <VERB>Q</VERB> et <VERB>M</VERB> telles que <VERB>A = Q*M</VERB>
    avec Im(<VERB>Q</VERB>)=Im(<VERB>A</VERB>) et ker(<VERB>M</VERB>)=ker(<VERB>A</VERB>),
    <VERB>Q</VERB> de rang maximal, et les lignes de <VERB>M</VERB> sont linéairement indépendantes, 
    <VERB>rk</VERB> = rank(<VERB>A</VERB>) = nombre de colonnes de <VERB>Q</VERB> =  nombre de lignes de <VERB>M</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>tol</VERB> = paramètre de tolérance (de l&apos;ordre de <VERB>%eps</VERB> par défaut).
    Le rang <VERB>rk</VERB> de <VERB>A</VERB> est considéré égal au nombre de ses valeurs singulières plus grandes que <VERB>norm(A)*tol</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    Si A est symétrique, <VERB>fullrf</VERB> renvoie <VERB>M=Q&apos;</VERB>.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
A=rand(5,2)*rand(2,5);
[Q,M]=fullrf(A);
norm(Q*M-A,1)
[X,d]=rowcomp(A);Y=X';
svd([A,Y(:,1:d),Q])        // Im(Q) = Im(A) = Im(Y(:,1:2))
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
